    "Radioisotope": "放射性同位素",
    ": An unstable isotope that undergoes radioactive decay.": "：发生放射性衰变的不稳定同位素。",
    "Isotope Notation": "同位素符号",
    ": Written as Element-mass number (e.g., Carbon-14) or with superscript mass number.": "：写为元素-质量数（例如 Carbon-14）或带有上标质量数。",
    "Percent Abundance": "百分比丰度",
    ": The percentage of each isotope found naturally; used to calculate atomic mass.": "：自然界中发现的每种同位素的百分比；用于计算原子质量。",
    ": Combining two lighter nuclei to form a heavier one; releases enormous energy.": "：结合两个较轻的原子核形成一个较重的原子核；释放巨大的能量。",
    ": In fission, released neutrons trigger further fission events, sustaining the reaction.": "：在裂变中，释放的中子引发更多的裂变事件，维持反应。",
    "Mass Defect": "质量亏损",
    ": The difference between the mass of the nucleus and the sum of its individual protons and neutrons ΓÇö converted to energy via E = mc┬▓.": "：原子核的质量与其单个质子和中子质量之和的差值 —— 通过 E = mc² 转化为能量。",
    "Nuclear Equation": "核反应方程",
    ": Shows the parent nucleus, emitted particle, and daughter nucleus. Mass and atomic numbers must balance.": "：显示母核、发射粒子和子核。质量数和原子序数必须平衡。",
    "Transmutation": "嬗变",
    ": The conversion of one element into another through nuclear reactions.": "：通过核反应将一种元素转化为另一种元素。",
    "Balancing Rule": "平衡规则",
    ": Sum of mass numbers on left = sum on right; sum of atomic numbers on left = sum on right.": "：左边的质量数之和 = 右边的质量数之和；左边的原子序数之和 = 右边的原子序数之和。",
    "Particle Symbols": "粒子符号",
    ": ╬▒ = Γü┤ΓééHe, ╬▓ = Γü░ΓéïΓéüe, ╬│ = Γü░ΓéÇ╬│, neutron = ┬╣ΓéÇn, proton = ┬╣Γéüp.": "：α = ⁴₂He, β = ⁰₋₁e, γ = ⁰₀γ, 中子 = ¹₀n, 质子 = ¹₁p。",
    "Alpha Decay (╬▒)": "Alpha 衰变 (α)",
    ": Emission of a helium-4 nucleus (┬▓ΓéäHe). Atomic number decreases by 2, mass number by 4.": "：发射氦-4 原子核 (²₄He)。原子序数减少 2，质量数减少 4。",
    "Beta Decay (╬▓)": "Beta 衰变 (β)",
    ": A neutron converts to a proton and emits an electron (Γü░ΓéïΓéüe). Atomic number increases by 1.": "：中子转化为质子并发射电子 (⁰₋₁e)。原子序数增加 1。",
    "Gamma Decay (╬│)": "Gamma 衰变 (γ)",
    ": Emission of high-energy electromagnetic radiation. No change in atomic or mass number.": "：发射高能电磁辐射。原子序数或质量数无变化。",
    "Penetrating Power": "穿透力",
    ": ╬▒ < ╬▓ < ╬│. Alpha stopped by paper; beta by aluminum; gamma by lead/concrete.": "：α < β < γ。Alpha 被纸阻挡；Beta 被铝阻挡；Gamma 被铅/混凝土阻挡。",
    "Nuclear Power": "核能",
    ": Fission of uranium-235 heats water to produce steam that drives turbines for electricity.": "：铀-235 的裂变加热水产生蒸汽，驱动涡轮机发电。",
    "Medical Uses": "医疗用途",
    ": Radioisotopes used in imaging (PET scans), cancer treatment (radiation therapy), and tracers.": "：放射性同位素用于成像（PET 扫描）、癌症治疗（放疗）和示踪剂。",
    "Carbon Dating": "碳定年法",
    ": Uses the decay of carbon-14 to determine the age of organic materials up to ~50,000 years.": "：利用碳-14 衰变测定距今约 50,000 年以内的有机物质的年龄。",
    "Food Irradiation": "食品辐照",
    ": Gamma rays kill bacteria in food to extend shelf life without making food radioactive.": "：Gamma 射线杀死食品中的细菌以延长保质期，而不会使食品具有放射性。",
    ": Formula": "：公式",
    ": Remaining = Original ├ù (┬╜)Γü┐, where n = number of half-lives elapsed.": "：剩余量 = 原始量 × (½)ⁿ，其中 n = 经过的半衰期次数。",
    ": Finding n": "：求 n",
